FT  09 JUL 92 / International Company News: Rio Algom in Chile move
RIO ALGOM, the Canadian mining company, is to invest Dollars 250m to develop
its wholly-owned Cerro Colorado copper mine in northern Chile, according to
Mr Fernando Porcile, Cerro Colorado's vice-president for operations, Reuter
reports from Santiago.
The Cerro Colorado open-pit mine will be managed by Rio Algom subsidiaries
RioChile and RioCerro and is expected to come on line in January of 1994,
with an initial production of 40,000 tonne SX-EW copper cathodes a year, Mr
Porcile said. However, production should eventually reach 60,000 tonnes a
year of copper cathode.
